Source: plpgsql-wrap
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~), pkg-config, libssl-dev
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/hexacluster/plpgsql_wrap/

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-plpgsql-wrap
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-plpgsql-wrap
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Oracle WRAP-equivalent PL/pgSQL language handler
 plpgsql_wrap stores PL/pgSQL procedure source as AES-256-GCM encrypted text in
 pg_proc.prosrc while keeping dump and restore workflows usable. The extension
 requires plpgsql and must be installed by a superuser.
